</p>
<p>Choosing the right words can be challenging, but the sincerity of your sentiment is paramount.  Avoid clichés or overly formal language.  Instead, focus on expressing genuine feelings of sadness, remembering positive aspects of the deceased, and offering support to the grieving individuals.  A simple, heartfelt message can hold more meaning than a long, impersonal one.  Always ensure your message is delivered with care and consideration, mindful of the recipient's emotional state.</p>
    

